movie_night.title: Movie Night!
movie_night.description: Why go out? Enjoy the cinematic experience from the comfort of your own living room with these big-screen movies and your favorite actors!

289816.title: Ghost In The Shell
289816.description: See the groundbreaking original before the release of the live-action remake starring Scarlett Johansson! It is 2029 and a female cyborg hunts a hacker who robs humans of their memories.

300448.title: Death At A Funeral
300448.description: After the unexpected death of a British patriarch, the dead man’s secrets leave the rest of his family with comical complications.

300452.title: The Man In The Iron Mask
300452.description: Three former musketeers attempt to unseat the tyrannical King Louis XIV and replace him with his alleged (and imprisoned) long lost twin.

306935.title: Lars and The Real Girl
306935.description: A delusional young man strikes up an unconventional relationship with a doll he finds on the Internet in this weird and warm comedy.

310136.title: Hotel Rwanda
310136.description: The true story of a brave hotel manager who risked his and his family’s lives to harbor over 1,000 refugees during the 1994 Rwandan genocide.

312179.title: Get Shorty
312179.description: A gangster goes to Hollywood to collect a debt and becomes a big-time producer when he realizes the movie business runs a lot like the mob.

312424.title: Ronin
312424.description: A team of international mercenaries and ex-special operatives is hired to track down and steal a mysterious briefcase in this action-thriller.

313931.title: Stir of Echoes
313931.description: After being hypnotized, Tom (Kevin Bacon) is haunted by terrifying visions that seem to be sending him a message from beyond.

316459.title: Cube
316459.description: Seven strangers find themselves imprisoned in a seemingly endless maze filled with deadly traps and must fight to escape,  despite the odds.

316461.title: Hard Candy
316461.description: A 14-year-old girl turns the tables on her would-be predator in this psychological thriller.

356528.title: Bowling for Columbine
356528.description: This documentary examines gun violence in the U.S. in relation to other countries, including the specific events that led to the Columbine massacre.

369729.title: The Thomas Crown Affair
369729.description: A millionaire playboy steals a priceless work of art and strikes up a fiery romance with the brilliant insurance investigator who works to take him down.

399691.title: Requiem for a Dream
399691.description: The lives of four people intertwine in this gut-wrenching, hypnotic tale of addiction and the devastation it has on their lives and those around them.

404623.title: Battle Royale
404623.description: A group of students from a Japanese high school are forced to compete in a battle, killing one another until only one is left standing.

405451.title: Rescue Dawn
405451.description: Based on the true story of a captured German-American fighter pilot in the Vietnam War who plans a daring escape after suffering abuse by his captors.

437414.title: Tucker & Dale vs. Evil
437414.description: A group of college kids mistake Tucker and Dale for killer hillbillies and, when one goes missing, the misconception grows—along with the body count.

438042.title: Goon
438042.description: A bouncer looking for purpose takes his fighting skills to the hockey rink where his epic brawls could make him a star—if he can learn how to skate.

439501.title: God Bless America
439501.description: Sick of the state of American culture, a downtrodden man and a plucky teenage girl launch a nationwide assault on the country's dumbest celebrities.

441470.title: Super Size Me
441470.description: Documentarian Morgan Spurlock explores the consequences on his health of a one-month diet consisting solely of items from the McDonald's menu.

448257.title: Amores Perros
448257.description: A horrific car accident connects the lives of three strangers: a lovesick dog fighter, an injured supermodel and a hitman running from his past.

448663.title: Leaving Las Vegas
448663.description: Determined to end it all, a committed drinker picks Vegas as his last stop, but he finds comfort with a kind prostitute who needs help of her own.

451666.title: Iron Sky
451666.description: The Nazis set up a secret base on the dark side of the moon in 1945 where they hide out and plan to return to power in 2018.

453693.title: Four Lions
453693.description: Four idiotic terrorists push their fuzzy dreams of jihad to the breaking point, as their beliefs and methods clash, in this far-out British farce.

456876.title: Bad Lieutenant: Port of Call New Orleans
456876.description: In the wake of Hurricane Katrina, a detective investigates the murders of several Senegalese immigrants.

456923.title: The Iceman
456923.description: Based on a shocking true story, a family man goes to great lengths to keep his work as a ruthless hitman a secret from the people he loves.

462517.title: The Illusionist
462517.description: In 19th century Vienna, a magician uses his talents to win the love of a noble woman but makes an enemy of the Crown Prince, now his romantic rival.

466212.title: Submarine
466212.description: A teenage boy aims to fulfill two dreams: to lose his virginity by his 16th birthday and to extinguish the flame between his mom and her ex-lover.

467588.title: The Man From Earth
467588.description: When colleagues throw a farewell bash for a retiring professor, the scholar reveals that he's had a stranger and far, far longer past than they knew.

475643.title: Stargate
475643.description: A historical expert and a military unit travel through a mysterious portal. They land in a bizarre world occupied by a dangerous and powerful being.

476644.title: The Boondock Saints
476644.description: Irish brothers try to clean up Boston’s underworld by knocking off gangsters and become local folk heroes, as an FBI agent traces their bloody trail.

478798.title: Hellraiser
478798.description: This cult classic tells the story of an unfaithful wife and her dead lover. The chilling nightmare introduces the iconic demon Pinhead.

480291.title: Triangle
480291.description: A woman's yacht trip turns to terror when she hits a storm in and her group is forced to board a seemingly deserted ocean liner to get to safety.

487757.title: Monster
487757.description: This true story of a woman with a tortured past traces her path from prostitution, to hopeful love, to vengeful murder, to becoming a serial killer.

507469.title: August: Osage County
507469.description: A dysfunctional mother’s emotional wounds against her adult children come to light as her family arrives at her Oklahoma home after a relative dies.

507477.title: The Ghost Writer
507477.description: A writer agrees to author the memoirs of a former Prime Minister only to learn that he is a war criminal and that his first writer was found dead.

512252.title: We Need to Talk About Kevin
512252.description: In this suspenseful and gripping psychological thriller, a mother contends for years with the increasing malevolence of her first-born child, Kevin.

520213.title: Train to Busan (Dubbed)
520213.description: A father and his estranged daughter are trapped on a speeding train full of fellow passengers when a zombie virus breaks out in South Korea.

522072.title: Silent Hill
522072.description: A mother desperately searches for her adopted daughter through a town that’s been possessed by an evil force. Can she find her in time?

523697.title: Only God Forgives
523697.description: A remorseful man with a shady past, who longs to escape his role in Bangkok's gritty criminal underbelly, gets sucked into a brutal cycle of revenge.

524652.title: Coherence
524652.description: When eight friends gather for a dinner party on the night of an astronomical event, a series of unusual circumstances tests their relationships.

525069.title: The Mountain II
525069.description: After training in a covert special operations squad, two unlikely best friends begin their first mission to rescue an ISIS-captured reporter in Iraq.

526368.title: The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo
526368.description: In this adaptation of Stieg Larsson's novel, hacker Lisbeth Salander teams up with a journalist to investigate a murder connected to a rich family.

539272.title: Evil Dead
539272.description: This update to the classic horror flick finds five friends in a cabin, about to unlock the curses that live inside the Book of the Dead.

539677.title: Lion
539677.description: A young man makes an emotional journey to reconnect with his birth family in India after being tragically separated from them years earlier.

543161.title: Apocalypto
543161.description: A Mayan warrior braves the treacherous jungle to fight off attacking members of an opposing tribe in order to save his family.

543873.title: Desperado
543873.description: Stunning visuals highlight this action classic as a lone and mysterious gunman shoots through a border town to find his girlfriend’s killer.

545512.title: Blade II
545512.description: Blade, the vampire-human hybrid, joins forces with a highly-skilled team of vampires to vanquish a new race of super vampires out for Armageddon.

550824.title: The Hunger Games
550824.description: In a dystopian future, 16-year-old Katniss volunteers to take her younger sister’s place in a battle where children must fight to stay alive.

550826.title: The Hunger Games: Catching Fire
550826.description: As Katniss and Peeta embark on their victory tour, President Snow plans an even deadlier new Hunger Games, which threatens the future of Panem.

550828.title: The Hunger Games: Mockingjay Part 2
550828.description: The celebrated movie series reaches its epic climax, as the brave Katniss fights to liberate Panem's citizens in a final showdown with President Snow.

551255.title: The Hunger Games: Mockingjay Part 1
551255.description: The franchise phenomenon continues, as Katniss, having survived The Hunger Games, rises with District 13 to battle the oppressive President Snow.

552216.title: Get the Gringo
552216.description: When a career criminal is nabbed by Mexican authorities and placed in a tough prison, he must  learn to survive, with the help of a young boy.

559330.title: Attack the Block
559330.description: A teen gang must defend their neighborhood from savage aliens who turn their apartment complex into an intergalactic warzone.

563166.title: 28 Weeks Later
563166.description: Six months after the military declares Britain safe from the mysterious rage virus that ravaged the nation, a terrifying new nightmare soon begins.

563168.title: Predators
563168.description: A mercenary reluctantly leads a group of elite warriors mysteriously brought together on a jungle planet where they are hunted by an alien race.

569769.title: Pandorum
569769.description: Panic and terror come fast as two astronauts wake up in an empty spacecraft with no memory of what happened - except that an evil entity is waiting.

571822.title: Ringu
571822.description: A determined aunt investigates how her niece died in such a sudden and unexplainable way. She uncovers a videotape with devastating consequences.

573585.title: Journey 2: The Mysterious Island
573585.description: When a young man receives his grandfather’s distress signal from a remote island, he heads off with his stepfather and a helicopter tour team.

574449.title: The Whole Nine Yards
574449.description: A notorious hitman moves in next door to a beleaguered dentist, which pulls the doctor out of his tedious life and into the organized crime world.

577525.title: Eden Lake
577525.description: A British couple takes a trip to a private and isolated lake quarry for a vacation, only to be targeted by a lurking mob of psychotic teenagers.

579647.title: Fahrenheit 9/11
579647.description: The definitive exposé revealing how and why the Bush Administration manufactured evidence to invade war in Iraq following the 2001 terrorist attacks.

580532.title: Lucky Number Slevin
580532.description: A mysterious man is roped into a dangerous feud between two rival crime kingpins, neither of whom can step foot outside for fear of assassination.

581905.title: Little Nicky
581905.description: After Satan refuses to retire his post in Hell, he sends the nicest and youngest of his sons to New York City to bring his two renegade brothers home.

582081.title: Vicky Cristina Barcelona
582081.description: Two American women are taken in by the splendor of Spain, but not as much as they are drawn to a rugged painter and his sultry former lover.

588499.title: I Saw the Devil (Dubbed)
588499.description: An elite federal agent becomes violently and darkly obsessed with a serial killer’s demise after the man murders his pregnant fiancée in cold blood.

589375.title: Tango & Cash
589375.description: A pair of rival LAPD cops become unlikely allies when both are framed and imprisoned on drug charges that force them in cahoots to clear their names.

591420.title: A Perfect Getaway
591420.description: A romantic Hawaiian vacation turns deadly for two pairs of lovers, when a duo of murderers begins targeting tourists who cannot escape the island.

595396.description: Tells the story of how Spartan King Leonidas and his soldiers numbering just 300 beat King Xerxes of Persia, with an army of hundreds of thousands.

599603.title: Contagion
599603.description: Oscar®-winning filmmaker Steven Soderbergh (Ocean's Eleven films, Traffic) returns to large-scale cinema with this global action thriller that revolves around the threat of a deadly outbreak of a fatal disease and the people determined to keep it at bay. As the fast-moving epidemic grows, the worldwide medical community races to find a cure and control the panic that spreads faster than the virus itself. At the same time, ordinary people struggle to survive in a society coming apart. A stellar international ensemble cast including Academy Award® winners Matt Damon, Gwyneth Paltrow, Kate Winslet, Marion Cotillard and nominees Jude Law and Laurence Fishburne portray the dedicated doctors at the CDC and World Health Organization who rush to contain the outbreak of a new virus. Tracking its source to Hong Kong and searching for a cure, these determined Samaritans do their utmost to limit deaths, civil unrest and the false rumors surrounding the disease in this viral outbreak drama with multiple plot lines in the style of Soderbergh's Oscar®-winning narcotics drama Traffic.

599629.title: Eyes Wide Shut
599629.description: Tom Cruise and Nicole Kidman star as a married couple entangled in an intricate web of jealousy and sexual obsession in Stanley Kubrick's final cinematic offering.  At a Christmas party hosted by wealthy, unconventional Victor Ziegler (Sydney Pollack), provocative advances and innocent flirtations arouse suspicion as high-society physician Dr. William Harford (Cruise) and his sexy wife, Alice (Kidman) watch each other from a distance. Alone later, this seemingly perfect couple confront their intimate sexual fantasies--which don't include each other.  Caught between reality and illusion, jealousy and obsession, William struggles with his inner urges. Will he act on his erotic fantasies or keep them hidden deep inside? Sometimes a man can see more clearly with his Eyes Wide Shut.

599994.title: Two Weeks Notice
599994.description: For five years Lucy has been treated more like a nanny than a Harvard-trained lawyer, chosen George's clothes, arranged his divorce, lost sleep and gained an ulcer, but now she's calling it quits. She gives George her Two Weeks Notice.  George finally agrees to let her go ... if she finds her own replacement. After a challenging search, Lucy hires an ambitious young lawyer with an obvious eye for her new boss. Now, as she joins her devoted boyfriend for an adventure at sea, Lucy is finally free of George. Or is she? With Lucy sailing out of his life, George must decide if it's ever too late to say "I love you."

599997.title: Wedding Crashers
599997.description: Owen Wilson (Starsky & Hutch) and Vince Vaughn (Old School) star as John Beckwith and Jeremy Klein, two partying divorce attorneys--and committed womanizers--who have figured out a surefire way to meet women: they crash weddings. But the guys' happy-go-lucky lives change abruptly when John unexpectedly falls in love with a bridesmaid (Rachel McAdams - The Notebook). Things become even more complicated when the men discover that the object of John's affection is the daughter of the United States Secretary of the Treasury (Christopher Walken - Catch Me If You Can) in the engaging romantic comedy Wedding Crashers.

601303.title: Hall Pass
601303.description: A pair of pals feeling restless in their otherwise happy marriages are given the green light to sleep with as many women as they can in one week.

602292.title: Blade
602292.description: A vampire-human hybrid uses his advanced powers and an arsenal of weapons to do battle with the bloodsucking monsters who threaten the living.

607451.title: E.T. The Extra-Terrestrial
607451.description: A boy forms a special bond with a sweet and gifted alien from another planet. He tries to keep it a secret, but he needs help to keep the visitor safe.

607952.title: True Lies
607952.description: A deadly and talented spy for the government hides his dangerous day job from his family, but his secret heroics take a toll on his marriage.

609721.title: The Karate Kid
609721.description: Jaden Smith stars in the 2010 reboot of the iconic franchise, this time as a young arrival in China who learns self-defense from a karate master.

610528.title: Blade Trinity
610528.description: An all-star sequel featuring Ryan Reynolds and Jessica Biel as vampire hunters who join Blade to stop a virus from being unleashed on the undead.

610572.title: Goodfellas
610572.description: Based on a true story, a young man rises up the ranks of a mob family over several years, dabbling in drugs, heists and murders along the way.

611206.title: The 13th Warrior
611206.description: Far from home, an exiled ambassador joins a fierce band of Viking warriors, who are attacked by ferocious creatures that devour every living thing.

612777.title: The Kitchen
612777.description: Set in 1978 Hell's Kitchen, this is the story of three housewives whose mobster husbands are sent to prison, leaving them to handle business.

616790.title: Metro
616790.description: Eddie Murphy teams with Michael Rapaport and Michael Wincott in this wildly entertaining, action-packed hit! Murphy plays Scott Roper, a fast-talking, wisecracking, on the edge hostage negotiator whose offbeat-but-winning style has made him San Francisco's top mediator! Roper will say...and do... absolutely anything to get his man. But when he comes face-to-face with a psychotic killer who's playing a lethal game of cat and mouse, he's finally met his match! Don't miss the excitement as the always amusing Murphy packs Metro with outrageous action that has critics and audiences cheering!

617447.title: Pretty Woman
617447.description: Julia Roberts stars as a witty prostitute who charms a serious businessman, as the two unlikely lovers fall for each other over the course of a week.

620886.title: The Road
620886.description: Following an apocalyptic event, a father and son travel through North America’s dangerous terrain in the hopes of reaching the ocean.

622678.title: Water for Elephants
622678.description: During the Great Depression, a veterinary student, recently orphaned and suddenly adrift, joins the circus and falls for the animal trainer’s wife.

622846.title: Australia
622846.description: With the threat of war looming, a landowner in Australia fights to keep her cattle and her land with the help of a seasoned ranch hand.

628970.title: Hellboy II: The Golden Army
628970.description: Hellboy and his crew of paranormal outcasts face off with forces of darkness in this imaginative adventure from visionary director Guillermo del Toro.

637106.title: Unknown
637106.description: A man awakens from a coma after a car wreck to find his wife doesn’t recognize him, his identity has been stolen, and hitmen are trying to kill him.

637827.title: Don Jon
637827.description: A Jersey guy addicted to porn meets a charming and beautiful woman whom he hopes to pursue a real relationship with, but his habits get in the way.

637929.title: Carlito's Way
637929.description: In 1975 NYC, a rehabilitated ex-con drug dealer determined to stay clean is tempted back into the life by an array of lowlifes and former associates.

638331.title: Cowboys & Aliens
638331.description: “Iron Man” director Jon Favreau directed this sci-fi Western with Daniel Craig and Harrison Ford squaring off against a massive intergalactic threat.

639313.title: The Infiltrator
639313.description: Based on a true story, a U.S. federal agent goes deep inside the inner workings of a notorious drug trafficking cartel in order to take it down.

639315.title: Knight of Cups
639315.description: A successful and self-indulgent Los Angeles screenwriter ambles through a world of wild parties and women in a quest to find love and himself.

639561.title: The Waterboy
639561.description: A socially awkward but well-meaning water boy's violent temper tantrums inspire a football coach to train him as his team’s defensive tackle.

639782.title: Ninja Assassin
639782.description: After a trained ninja leaves behind his former life, he works with a Europol agent to take down the hired killers who taught him everything he knows.

639974.title: To Wong Foo, Thanks for Everything! Julie Newmar
639974.description: John Leguizamo, Wesley Snipes, and Patrick Swayze are triple threats in this road trip romp about three drag queens who get stranded in a small town.

640031.title: Blackfish
640031.description: Award-winning documentary about the ethics of taking killer whales captive, especially after a loving trainer’s public death in a Sea World enclosure.

642254.title: The Girl with All the Gifts
642254.description: In a bleak future, mankind has succumbed to a fungus that turns everyone into flesh-eating monsters, until an immune child is discovered.

642272.title: I'm Not There
642272.description: The multifaceted life of Bob Dylan is examined through several variations of his own personality and career, embodied by six different characters.

642290.title: Rob Zombie's Halloween
642290.description: This remake of the classic finds Michael Myers after he’s released from a 17-year stay at the mental institution, already on a new killing spree.

643528.title: Beaches
643528.description: A lifelong friendship between two women, one a demure, privileged socialite, the other a bold, struggling singer, takes unexpected twists and turns.

647464.title: Hide and Seek
647464.description: In the wake of his wife’s suicide, a psychiatrist becomes powerless to help his young daughter cope as she turns to what began as an imaginary friend.

647479.title: Sister Act 2: Back in the Habit
647479.description: A Las Vegas showgirl-turned-singing nun becomes a run-down Catholic school’s only hope of reviving its music program and keeping its doors open.

647690.title: What About Bob?
647690.description: A month-long family vacation in New Hampshire becomes a psychiatrist’s undoing when his most dependent patient tracks him down at his rental property.

651086.title: Hancock
651086.description: A sarcastic, hard-living, misunderstood superhero, whose antics caused him to fall out of favor with the public, saves someone who might save him.

651094.title: Lake Placid
651094.description: At a serene Maine lake, a 30-foot reptilian eating machine hungers for a fragile paleontologist on her first field assignment and a tasty billionaire.

651120.title: The Tourist
651120.description: An American tourist visiting Italy to mend a broken heart is seduced by a beautiful woman, who ensnares him in an international criminal plot.

655009.title: Role Models
655009.description: A destruction of property offense lands a pair of energy drink sales reps a community service sentence as unlikely mentors in a Big Brother program.

655363.title: We Bought a Zoo
655363.description: A single dad set out to give his family a fresh start by uprooting them to the Southern California country to a home in the middle of a neglected zoo.

657674.title: The Edge
657674.description: A plane crash in the Alaskan wilderness pits two enemies and a billionaire against a blood-thirsty Kodiak bear in a brutal struggle for survival.

658082.title: To Die For
658082.description: Suzanne is dead set on being a famous TV reporter. When her husband asks her to give up her dream, she plots against him with a love-struck teenager.

661142.title: The Twilight Saga: Eclipse
661142.description: The third film in the Twilight franchise. Torn between Edward and Jacob, Bella must also confront a vengeful vampire and a string of grisly murders.

661144.title: The Twilight Saga: Breaking Dawn: Part 1
661144.description: The fourth film in the Twilight franchise. A marriage, honeymoon and child bring unforeseen and shocking developments for Bella and Edward.

663440.title: Dead Man Down
663440.description: A hitman for a New York crime lord is seduced and blackmailed by a victim seeking retribution who leads him on a violent and cathartic revenge spree.

663814.title: The Sisters Brothers
663814.description: Brothers and assassins Eli and Charlie Sisters pursue a prospector across the American Northwest in this witty reimagining of the cinematic Western.

664749.title: 10 Things I Hate About You
664749.description: On the first day at his new school, Cameron instantly falls for Bianca, the gorgeous girl of his dreams. The only problem? She isn't allowed to date.

665462.title: Apollo 13
665462.description: A routine space flight becomes a desperate battle of survival in this breathtaking and true-story of adventure, courage, and faith.

665877.title: Season of the Witch
665877.description: Two 14th-century Crusaders are tasked with routing a suspected witch to a distant monastery to let monks determine if she caused the Black Plague.

667422.title: Pacific Rim
667422.description: With alien invaders rising from the sea, a washed-up former pilot and an untested trainee use massive robots to combat the apocalyptic threat.

670370.title: Brightburn
670370.description: What if a child from another world crash-landed on Earth, but instead of becoming a hero to mankind, he proved to be something far more sinister?

672287.title: The Angry Birds Movie
672287.description: When mysterious green piggies visit an island populated by flightless birds, it's up to three unlikely outcasts to figure out what the pigs are up to.

672301.title: The 40-Year-Old Virgin
672301.description: Nice guy Andy has lived his whole life without "doing it." Now, his misguided pals are helping him reverse his fortunes—and maybe even find true love.

672442.title: Dredd
672442.description: The head of Mega City One’s elite police force becomes the city’s last hope when a sex worker-turned-drug dealer aims to take over the city.

676660.title: The Babadook
676660.description: A mother struggles to protect her son from an evil supernatural entity that has escaped the pages of a children's book and is lurking in their home.

676665.title: The Death of Stalin
676665.description: Follows the wild scramble for power inside the Council of Ministers upon the sudden illness and death of Soviet dictator Joseph Stalin in 1953.

676695.title: Terminal
676695.description: A mystery inside a train terminal ensnares a dying teacher, two assassins on a mission, an enigmatic janitor and a waitress leading a double life.

676725.title: Boyhood
676725.description: Richard Linklater's acclaimed hit, filmed over twelve years with the same cast, is a groundbreaking celebration of life, growing up, and parenting.

676860.title: Bone Tomahawk
676860.description: When a group of individuals kidnaps settlers from a small town, an unlikely team of gunslingers, led by Sheriff Hunt, sets out to bring them home.

678881.title: Paul Blart: Mall Cop
678881.description: When a shopping mall is taken over by a gang of organized crooks, it's up to a mild-mannered security guard to save the day.

680568.title: Super
680568.description: A super-entertaining action fantasy about a down-on-his-luck fry cook who becomes a homegrown masked avenger and puts an end to crimes.

682190.title: Hesher
682190.description: After losing his mom in a car crash and drifting further from his forlorn dad, 10-year-old T.J meets Hesher, who makes his life even more chaotic.

685920.title: Brawl in Cell Block 99
685920.description: After he's fired from his mechanic gig, a hot-tempered ex-boxer enters the drug-running game which lands him in the battleground of a brutal prison.

686278.title: Doom
686278.description: Based on the hit videogame, this adventure begins when a call for help from a research station on Mars sends a team of mercenary Marines into action.

690311.title: The Reader
690311.description: In post-WWII Germany, a law student finds the older woman with whom he had an affair eight years ago, among Nazi prison guards being tried for murder.

694011.title: Vice
694011.description: This acclaimed biopic explores how Dick Cheney quietly wielded immense power as George W. Bush's Vice President, reshaping the U.S. and the globe.

694768.title: American Pie
694768.description: The stakes are high when four friends make the pact to lose their virginity by prom night in this romp about high school, band camp and apple pie.

696058.title: American Pie 2
696058.description: A year after their prom night misadventures, the gang reunites for a summer they'll never forget at a beach house they turn into party central.

696806.title: A Walk to Remember
696806.description: North Carolina teens Landon Carter and Jamie Sullivan are thrown together after one gets into trouble and is sentenced to community service.

698792.title: Assault on Precinct 13
698792.description: Two men on opposite sides of the law join forces in an epic New Year's Eve battle against an enemy that doesn’t follow the code of cop or criminal.

698965.title: The Jackal
698965.description: An engaging suspense thriller about a ruthless assassin hired to eliminate a powerful, high-ranking official in the U.S. government.

698980.title: Dead Silence
698980.description: After the murder of his wife, a man returns to his hometown and uncovers the terrifying legend of Mary Shaw, a cursed ventriloquist from the 40s.

698981.title: Drag Me to Hell
698981.description: When loan officer Christine decides to evict an older woman, she becomes the victim of an evil spirit determined to drag her to hell.

701396.title: Lamborghini: The Man Behind the Legend
701396.description: This thrilling, high-speed biopic reveals Ferruccio Lamborghini’s dream of making the world’s fastest car—and beating rival Enzo Ferrari to it.

720947.title: Little Man
720947.description: After a stolen diamond gets stashed in the home of a husband and wife, a pint-sized jewel thief poses as the world's ugliest baby to get it back.

723250.title: Bend It Like Beckham
723250.description: Despite the wishes of their traditional families, two young women from different walks of life aim for a career in professional soccer.

723254.title: Master and Commander: The Far Side of the World
723254.description: A distinguished young captain of the British Navy leads his crew on a mission to take a French vessel with a reputation for sinking British ships.

723256.title: Red Sparrow
723256.description: A Russian intelligence officer tasked with seducing a CIA agent finds her mission and its objective threatened when they both fall for each other.

723828.title: The Best Offer
723828.description: An eccentric and lonely art auctioneer becomes obsessed with a reclusive heiress he can’t see and who’s hired him to value her family’s collection.

724340.title: The Autopsy of Jane Doe
724340.description: Coroners are mystified by an unidentified corpse until a series of terrifying events makes it clear that cadaver Jane Doe is not actually dead.

724377.title: Downfall
